The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Molest slur on doctors
                                                                                                               Molest slur on doctors
                            
	Calcutta, March 11: Two doctors of a nursing home on New Town Road have been accused of molesting a patient.        
	The husband of the patient has lodged a complaint against the doctors at Baguiati police station, alleging that his wife was assaulted last night in the nursing home in Teghoria.        
	The husband has complained that he tried to speak to his wife last night but the clinic officials did not allow him to do so. This morning, the patient broke down and told her husband that she had been molested by the doctors.        
	She was admitted to the nursing home on Sunday with respiratory problems. Officials at Baguiati police station said investigations were on.                                                                                                                                                                             
